## Example 22a/b) (union distributes over intersection)

```elixir
res = ~p"""
#{set_theory}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  (union @ a @ (inter @ b @ c)) = (inter @ (union @ a @ b) @ (union @ a @ c))
).
""" |> prove

res |> format_result |> IO.puts
```

```elixir
res = ~p"""
#{set_theory}
#{leibniz1}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  l @ (union @ a @ (inter @ b @ c)) @ (inter @ (union @ a @ b) @ (union @ a @ c))
).
""" |> prove

res |> format_result |> IO.puts
```

```elixir
res = ~p"""
#{set_theory}
#{leibniz2}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  l @ (union @ a @ (inter @ b @ c)) @ (inter @ (union @ a @ b) @ (union @ a @ c))
).
""" |> prove

res |> format_result |> IO.puts
```

```elixir
res = ~p"""
#{set_theory}
#{leibniz3}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  l @ (union @ a @ (inter @ b @ c)) @ (inter @ (union @ a @ b) @ (union @ a @ c))
).
""" |> prove

res |> format_result |> IO.puts
```

```elixir
res = ~p"""
#{set_theory}
#{andrews}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  a @ (union @ sa @ (inter @ b @ c)) @ (inter @ (union @ sa @ b) @ (union @ sa @ c))
).
""" |> prove

res |> format_result |> IO.puts
```

```elixir
res = ~p"""
#{set_theory}
#{extensional}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  e @ (union @ a @ (inter @ b @ c)) @ (inter @ (union @ a @ b) @ (union @ a @ c))
).
""" |> prove

res |> format_result |> IO.puts
```

